munity working together to support policymakers to develop health systems that are equitable efficient responsive and transparent at the steering committee meeting in bangkok in late january the appointed members of the apo research advisory group met for the first time including karen eggleston director of stanford's asia health policy program the apo has prepared two health systems in transition reports providing in depth profiles of the health systems of the philippines and fiji additional country health system profiles and policy briefs will be published in 2012 the research and analysis generated by the observatory is considered as a public good and is freely available at the apo website html+ read more asia pacific observatory of health systems and policies http www wpro who int asia_pacifi search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest youku victor koo announces partnership at sprie's china 2.0 sprie in the news computerworld hong kong on october 19 2010 announcing the asia pacific health policy forum march 10 2008 ahpp news conference on healthcare payment incentives in the asia pacific january 31 2008 ahpp announcement new book examines the cross currents of growing regional integration and rising nationalism in northeast asia october 24 2007 news aparc renamed the walter h shorenstein asia pacific research center september 20 2005 press release new name for the asia pacific research center august 11 2005 news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
